The paper proposes a method for jointly optimizing the physical design of a robot and its control policy using reinforcement learning. This work is primarily focused on robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG), as it involves training a neural network controller using reinforcement learning. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the design of the robot, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach in the context of legged locomotion, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) for analyzing the robot's movement.
